url: "https://aethersystems.io"
abstract: >-
  Conscience Architecture (ConA) is a framework for individual behavioral
  modeling in adversarial, multi-party environments. It specifies the
  architectural conditions — edge sovereignty, tiered access, zero-drift
  alignment, the Verified Catalog principle, and the right of withdrawal —
  under which a longitudinal behavioral model of a human operator (a
  "Relational Twin") cannot be inverted, extracted, cloned, or weaponized
  against the operator. ConA is the adversarial-environment companion to
  Consciousness Architecture (CA), which addresses sealed, mission-aligned
  environments such as long-duration spaceflight.
keywords:
  - behavioral modeling
  - edge sovereignty
